that.”

“Who?” asked Martha. “I don’t understand whom you’re speaking about.”

“I mean him. If he should come home all at once. He has such a stealthy way of opening doors.”

“Oh, you are speaking of my late husband, oh, I see,” said Martha in a smoky voice. “No, my deceased was always a man of precision. He would let me know—no, no, Franz, not now, after supper, perhaps. I think he meant to be an example to his little wife, who otherwise might visit him—I said no—w